&lt;h4&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;What we&#39;d like to see&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: Minimum of 3 years in Linux systems administration, with at least 1-2 years in team leadership or technical management roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Storage: Proven experience operating Ceph clusters.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automation &amp;amp; Configuration: Strong command of configuration management tools (Puppet, Saltstack) and orchestration tools (Ansible, Terraform).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Scripting: Advanced proficiency in BASH and Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cloud &amp;amp; Virtualization: Hands-on experience with OpenStack.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Observability: Proficiency with monitoring tools such as Prometheus and Grafana.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Expectations&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Being part of a multidisciplinary team passionate about technology, with an open and dynamic culture, where experimentation and discussion are encouraged to progress at work, always with respect and inclusion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We offer personalised career plans, annual performance evaluations and programmes to develop skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We operate in Spanish and English and therefore provide unlimited language training. We work on international projects and define best practices with United Internet partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have flexible start and finish times, respecting a schedule of meetings in the central part of the morning and a range of work from 7 a.m. to 9 p.m. with a hybrid model in one of our offices (Alcobendas, Valencia, Barcelona, Seville or Logroño).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
